      "content": "It makes sense that you feel this way, but the engine isn't actually dead; it's just covered in soot and rust from the stress you've been carrying. The \"you\" that mattered hasn't evaporated, it's been pushed into hiding because it's protecting itself from the pain you're feeling. You don't need to find a new purpose today, you just need to let someone help you clear the debris so you can feel the warmth of your own existence again.",
